OL,3,CHe lost his family, then his legs: One
OL,4,Cchild's experience in Gaza
OL,6,FWith no bomb shelter, we don't know if
OL,7,Fthey are asleep when their home is one
OL,8,Fof the first to be hit in the early
OL,9,Fhours of October 8.
OL,11,FWhat we do know is that, despite the
OL,12,Fdesperate attempts of the emergency
OL,13,Fservices - which are still fully
OL,14,Ffunctioning on that first night -
OL,15,FAhmad's mother, father and brother are
OL,16,Fgone.
OL,18,FAhmad's beloved grandparents are also
OL,19,Fkilled.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/14
