OL,3,CHe lost his family, then his legs: One
OL,4,Cchild's experience in Gaza
OL,6,FThere is no one left to explain to
OL,7,FAhmad what is happening as he is taken
OL,8,Fto the Indonesian hospital, in the
OL,9,FGaza strip, to be treated for his
OL,10,Finjuries, which are miraculously only
OL,11,Fminor.
OL,13,FOn the streets outside, the funerals
OL,14,Fof his family quickly take place as
OL,15,Fthe bodies of his parents are carried
OL,16,Fthrough the streets.
OL,18,FAhmad calls repeatedly for his mum,
OL,19,FDiana, as the Israeli bombardment
OL,20,Fintensifies.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/14
