OL,3,CHe lost his family, then his legs: One
OL,4,Cchild's experience in Gaza
OL,6,FOnce in Nuseirat, they take refuge in
OL,7,Fa UN-run school which has become home
OL,8,Fto hundreds of displaced Gazans.
OL,10,FWhen he cries out at night it is his
OL,11,Fyoungest uncle, Saleh, who comforts
OL,12,Fhim. The pair become inseparable.
OL,14,FSaleh is aged 26 and has just got
OL,15,Fengaged to be married. He is set to
OL,16,Fbecome Ahmad's guardian and primary
OL,17,Fcarer.
OL,19,FOn November 13, the pair walk to the
OL,20,Fmarket to try to buy food. It's the
OL,21,Flast time Ahmad walks anywhere.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G8/14
