OL,3,CHe lost his family, then his legs: One
OL,4,Cchild's experience in Gaza
OL,6,FThey have no choice but to amputate
OL,7,Fhis legs at the thigh before he's
OL,8,Fmoved to a bed in a hospital corridor.
OL,10,FIt is impossible to comfort the little
OL,11,Fboy who has lost everyone he loves and
OL,12,Fis in unimaginable pain.
OL,14,FBut his uncle Ibrahim tries, stroking
OL,15,Fhis nephew's hair as he cries out in
OL,16,Fpain.
OL,18,FIt takes almost two weeks to get Ahmad
OL,19,Fout of Gaza - doctors say if he stays
OL,20,Fhe has little chance of surviving.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G10/14
