OL,3,CHe lost his family, then his legs: One
OL,4,Cchild's experience in Gaza
OL,6,FIbrahim always calms him with cuddles,
OL,7,Fwhispering "It'll be alright, habibti".
OL,9,FThe years ahead will be full of
OL,10,Fpainful surgeries and Ahmad will have
OL,11,Fto face them without the parents he
OL,12,Floved so much by his side.
OL,14,FGiven all that he's lost it's
OL,15,Fimpossible to describe him as lucky.
OL,17,FBut he is at least safe now, unlike so
OL,18,Fmany children like him, still trapped
OL,19,Fin Gaza and struggling to survive.
